1. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper focuses on using robots to perform peg-in-hole assembly tasks, which falls under the domain of robotics. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper uses two in-hand cameras to account for position uncertainty and a deep neural network for learning-based visual servoing, which are both related to computer vision. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses a deep neural network for learning-based visual servoing, which falls under the domain of machine learning. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper uses a deep neural network for learning-based visual servoing, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper uses a force-torque sensor and impedance control to perform the peg-in-hole task, which are related to systems and control.
